  "prompt": "What is buried or was buried under Solomon's Temple?",
  "response": "The area where Solomon's Temple was built is of considerable historical and archaeological interest, but there are no definitive records of what exactly may be buried there. The temple, built in Jerusalem in the 10th century BCE according to biblical accounts, was said to be the dwelling place of the Ark of the Covenant, which itself was believed to contain sacred items such as the tablets of the Ten Commandments.\n\nAfter the destruction of the First Temple by the Babylonians in 586 BCE, the fate of the Ark and other artifacts is unclear. Some traditions and folklore suggest that the Ark was hidden or taken away before the destruction, leading to various theories about its possible burial or concealment locations.\n\nExcavations in and around the Temple Mount area have been limited and sensitive due to the site's religious significance. Some have suggested that there could be ancient artifacts, treasures, or remains of the temple structure itself buried beneath, but none have been conclusively proven.\n\nOverall, while there are many theories and stories about what might be buried under Solomon's Temple or the Temple Mount, as of now, there's no concrete evidence to support any specific claims.",
